"title": "7953: mission, of the church",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7953",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The continuation of Jesus Christ's mission through his followers. Believers are empowered by the Holy Spirit and sent out by Christ to bear witness to him and to preach, heal, teach, baptise and make disciples of all peoples.</p>\n<h2>The power and authority of the church's mission</h2>\n<h3>Believers are sent out by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:16\">JHN 15:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:37-Matt9:38\">MAT 9:37–9:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:1-Luke10:3\">LUK 10:1–10:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:36-John4:38\">JHN 4:36–4:38</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are given authority by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1\">LUK 9:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1\">MAT 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18\">MAT 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:7\">MRK 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:17-Mark16:18\">MRK 16:17–16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:17-Luke10:19\">LUK 10:17–10:19</a></p>\n<h3>Believers continue Jesus Christ's mission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:21\">JHN 20:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:18\">JHN 17:18</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are empowered by the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:49\">LUK 24:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:22\">JHN 20:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:31\">ACT 4:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">HEB 2:4</a></p>\n<h2>The task of the church in mission</h2>\n<h3>Making disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:41-Acts2:42\">ACT 2:41–2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:15\">ACT 14:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:14-Acts16:15\">ACT 16:14–16:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:8\">ACT 18:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:14-Rom10:15\">ROM 10:14–10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:2-1John1:3\">1JN 1:2–1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Preaching and healing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:2\">LUK 9:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:7-Matt10:8\">MAT 10:7–10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:20\">MRK 16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:6\">LUK 9:6</a></p>\n<h3>Proclaiming the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:24\">ACT 20:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:40\">ACT 8:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:9\">ROM 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:20\">ROM 15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:11\">2TI 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>Bearing witness to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:30-Acts5:32\">ACT 5:30–5:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:48\">LUK 24:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26-John15:27\">JHN 15:26–15:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:20\">ACT 4:20</a></p>\n<h3>Bringing honour to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:10-Eph3:11\">EPH 3:10–3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:8\">JHN 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:12\">1PE 2:12</a></p>\n<h2>The universal scope of the church's mission</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:47\">LUK 24:47</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:14\">MAT 24:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:10\">MRK 13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:15\">MRK 16:15</a></p>\n<h2>The church reaching out in mission</h2>\n<h3>To the Jews</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:5-Matt10:6\">MAT 10:5–10:6</a></strong> <em>The disiples' mission began with the Jews.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:9-Matt10:15\">MAT 10:9–10:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:8-Mark6:11\">MRK 6:8–6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:3-Luke9:5\">LUK 9:3–9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:4-Luke10:12\">LUK 10:4–10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:19\">ACT 11:19</a> <em>The scattered believers at first preached only to Jews.</em></p>\n<h3>To the Samaritans</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:4-Acts8:8\">ACT 8:4–8:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:14-Acts8:17\">ACT 8:14–8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:25\">ACT 8:25</a></p>\n<h3>To the Gentiles</h3>\n<p>Paul as the apostle to the Gentiles:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:15\">ACT 9:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:13\">ROM 11:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:16\">ROM 15:16</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:34-Acts10:35\">ACT 10:34–10:35</a> <em>Peter preaches to Cornelius and his family</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:20-Acts11:21\">ACT 11:20–11:21</a> <em>Scattered believers preach to the Gentiles</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:1-Acts13:3\">ACT 13:1–13:3</a> <em>Paul begins his first missionary journey (with Barnabas)</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:40-Acts15:41\">ACT 15:40–15:41</a> <em>Paul begins his second missionary journey (with Silas)</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:9-Acts16:10\">ACT 16:9–16:10</a> <em>Paul is called to preach the gospel in Macedonia</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:23\">ACT 18:23</a> <em>Paul's third missionary journey</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:31\">ACT 28:31</a> <em>Paul preaches the gospel in Rome.</em></p>\n<h2>Missions undertaken by church officials</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:22-Acts11:23\">ACT 11:22–11:23</a> <em>Barnabas is sent to Antioch to strengthen the new church.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:30\">ACT 11:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:25\">ACT 12:25</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:22-Acts15:23\">ACT 15:22–15:23</a> <em>Judas and Silas are sent to Antioch with a letter from the apostles and elders.</em></p>",
